                    <item_0
                        jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                        sling:resourceType="core/franklin/components/block/v1/block/item"
                        model="text-container-text"
                        modelFields="[text]"
                        name="Text Container Text"
                        text="&lt;p>Other key features of the school include:&lt;/p>&lt;p>&lt;ul> &lt;li>A 3,300-square-foot cafeteria with floor-to-ceiling windows&lt;/li> &lt;li>Hot meal service, which wasn’t available at the former school&lt;/li> &lt;li>A collegiate style gathering place known as the “Learning Stairs” where students, teachers and staff can meet for announcements and informal events&lt;/li> &lt;li>A new music room, fitness center and 1,800-square-foot media center&lt;/li> &lt;li>Six new science labs and new maker spaces, enabling teachers to expand academic curricula&lt;/li> &lt;li>Private spaces where students can meet with occupational therapists, social workers and nurses, keeping social-emotional learning and physical health in mind&lt;/li> &lt;li>The district’s first, custom-built sensory room – a therapeutic space which includes both calming and active sides to support students’ well-being&lt;/li> &lt;/ul>&lt;/p>&lt;p>“The new Neal Math and Science Academy provides a modernized learning environment that reflects the potential of North Chicago students and AbbVie’s culture of giving back to our communities,” said Laura Schumacher, vice chairman, external affairs and chief legal officer, AbbVie.&lt;/p>"/>
                </block_10>
